## Step 5: Update `api/subscribe.ts` to also store leads in DB

Read the current file. After a successful email send, also insert the lead into the `leads` table. Add this after the Resend calls succeed:

```typescript
// After successful email send, store lead in DB
if (process.env.DATABASE_URL) {
  try {
    const { Pool } = await import("pg");
    const pool = new Pool({ connectionString: process.env.DATABASE_URL, ssl: { rejectUnauthorized: false } });
    await pool.query(
      `INSERT INTO leads (email, score, category) VALUES ($1, $2, $3) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING`,
      [email, score, getCategoryLabel(score)]
    );
    await pool.end();
  } catch {
    // Non-blocking — don't fail the request if DB insert fails
  }
}
```

